                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &amp; Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Whether you choose to read a book on a park bench or utilize one of the unique amenities, you'll be glad to know that Hawkwood is home to many fantastic recreational possibilities.</p>
                    <p>There are several parks within the community, such as Hawkmount Green NW playground, Hawkmount Close NW playground, Hawkstone Close NW playground, and Hawkbury Close playground.</p>
                    <p>Apart from these open spaces, you can also find several parks close to the community, such as Hawkwood Community Park, Hawkwood Upland Ravine, Hawkcliffe Ravine, and Crowfoot park.</p>
                    <p>Apart from spending leisure time at any of the several parks and playgrounds in the vicinity, Hawkwood residents can also access several facilities offered by the community association. Community members also have access to various shopping alternatives.</p>
                    <p>Here are all the amenities and facilities you can access while living in Hawkwood:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Aside from sidewalks and parks, Hawkwood homeowners have access to several paved walking routes that weave through the green areas that separate each neighbourhood.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Hawkwood retail plazas provide convenience stores, dry cleaners, restaurants, and daycare services.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Additional shopping is minutes away at the Crowfoot Shopping Center - featuring Safeway, Co-op and Rona among its numerous businesses.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Just north of Hawkwood is the recently created Beacon Hill shopping complex, which includes anchor stores like Costco, Home Depot, and Canadian Tire.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">The Hawkwood Community Association provides a variety of recreation opportunities for its residents who like sports and active interests.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Tennis facilities, a skate park, basketball courts, and many municipal parks are among the several sporting spaces.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Residents can also participate in baseball, badminton, yoga, and soccer.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Boys can participate in the Boy Scouts programme, while girls can participate in the Girl Guides.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">It is next to the neighbouring Crowfoot Centre, which has a multi-screen cinema as well as several stores and restaurants.</li>
                    </ul>
