        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Hawkwood was founded in 1981 and named after John and Joseph Hawkwood, the original landowners.</p>
            <p>In 2005, the average household income of families in this neighbourhood was $96,806, and 9.1% of people were considered to be low-income. Immigrants amounted to 29.6% of the total population in 2000. Condominiums or flats accounted for 4.1% of the buildings. While 5.5% of the housing was rented, the rest was occupied by homeowners.</p>
            <p>French, Cantonese, Mandarin, Arabic, German, Korean, and Spanish are the most prevalent languages spoken by locals in the community.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 44.5 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Hawkwood has an average of 3 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 49% male and 50% female residents. Approximately 14% of the residents of Hawkwood are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Melcor Developments began developing Hawkwood real estate in the early 1980s, and it immediately became a popular destination for families. Condominiums in Hawkwood are a fantastic alternative for first-time homeowners who want to be close to public transportation and shopping while still enjoying the laid-back lifestyle of a suburb.</p>
            <p>Hawkwood houses were built keeping families in mind. 3 to 4 bedrooms, huge living areas, and wide lots are typical features of these enormous split-level homes. The two-car garages are ideal for storing outdoor equipment or carefully putting cars away at night in the colder months to keep them warm.</p>
